1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:03,067
<i> You said he was okay!</i>

2
00:00:03,067 --> 00:00:05,167
<i>You said he was coming home
to us!</i>

3
00:00:05,167 --> 00:00:06,600
<i> You lied!</i>

4
00:00:07,667 --> 00:00:09,167
<i> You're so stupid, Martin!</i>

5
00:00:09,167 --> 00:00:10,133
<i>Rather than
punishing yourself,</i>

6
00:00:10,133 --> 00:00:12,400
<i>give honor and justice
to Leon's death.</i>

7
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,100
<i> Sandro.</i>

8
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:16,267
<i>- Sandro Soliman.
- He's alive.</i>

9
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:19,567
<i>They thought they could
get away from me.</i>

10
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:21,267
<i> I will be watching you.</i>

11
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:23,667
<i>You're going home.
We're going home.</i>

12
00:00:23,667 --> 00:00:25,467
<i>As long as
the hotel isn't safe,</i>

13
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:27,167
<i> I won't leave my brothers.</i>

14
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:29,033
<i>This is the last chance.
Just think of this</i>

15
00:00:29,033 --> 00:00:32,500
<i>as our last chance
to help our brothers.</i>

16
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:33,667
<i>- Hey!
- Oh!</i>

17
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,233
<i> Trixie, run!</i>

18
00:00:36,667 --> 00:00:39,233
<i> Argh! Help!</i>

19
00:00:39,233 --> 00:00:41,133
<i>Trixie! Where are you
and Cheska?</i>

20
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:45,067
<i>All the clues
to finding the treasure...</i>

21
00:00:45,067 --> 00:00:46,467
<i> You have to give it to him.</i>

22
00:00:47,233 --> 00:00:49,033
<i> In exchange for our lives.</i>

23
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:50,033
<i>- Cheska!
- Trixie!</i>

24
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:52,567
<i> - Cheska!
- Who kidnapped your sister?!</i>

25
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:57,200
<i> The third map...</i>

26
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:02,433
How can we save Cheska?

27
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:05,167
That was Sandro, right?

28
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:08,100
Sandro kidnapped
our sisters?

29
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:10,767
Him and Andy.

30
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:13,467
They're the only ones
who can do this.

31
00:01:13,467 --> 00:01:15,100
And they're asking
for the map.

32
00:01:17,367 --> 00:01:19,767
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

33
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:21,667
- Jade.
- Jade, did you get it?

34
00:01:21,667 --> 00:01:24,533
Yes, here. Wait.

35
00:01:24,533 --> 00:01:28,400
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,333
Why?

37
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:32,133
What-- What happened?

38
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:37,167
Someone kidnapped
Cheska and Trixie.

39
00:01:37,167 --> 00:01:39,400
And they're asking for the map
in exchange for their lives.

40
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:41,633
What?! Is it Sandro?!

41
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:46,367
Where is it? We're going
to send it to him.

42
00:01:46,367 --> 00:01:47,633
- Martin--
- Come on.

43
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:51,433
We're not going to give this
to him.

44
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:54,100
As I was saying...

45
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:56,633
We're going to give it.

46
00:01:58,133 --> 00:02:00,633
- I'll call him to--
- I said we're not giving this.

47
00:02:00,633 --> 00:02:02,700
- Are you serious?
- Yes, I am!

48
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:04,567
You're really messed up,
aren't you?!

49
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:06,267
Let go of me.

50
00:02:06,267 --> 00:02:07,800
You're deciding
based on your emotions.

51
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,500
You are not thinking rationally.

52
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:14,333
Our sisters' lives are
at stake here.

53
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:17,167
But you! Money's still
on your mind, huh?!

54
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:20,133
- [KIKO] That's enough!
- [GEORGIA] Stop it!

55
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:22,100
[JADE] Now isn't the time
to argue.

56
00:02:22,867 --> 00:02:24,833
We don't care
about the money anymore.

57
00:02:24,833 --> 00:02:28,467
What matters now are
the lives of our sisters!

58
00:02:28,467 --> 00:02:31,833
[GEORGIA] Stop it.
Enough, please!

59
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:35,233
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:37,233
Is that all I am to you?

61
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:41,633
Someone greedy?

62
00:02:42,467 --> 00:02:43,433
Why?

63
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,833
- Are you not?
- Shut up.

64
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:49,133
- That's enough! Stop it!
- Come on! Do it again!

65
00:02:49,167 --> 00:02:52,133
- You're fighting now?!
- But they're becoming too much!

66
00:02:53,233 --> 00:02:55,233
How dare you call me greedy?

67
00:02:55,233 --> 00:02:57,233
After everything
we've been through?!

68
00:02:57,233 --> 00:02:59,767
I hope you understand that
our sisters are missing!

69
00:02:59,767 --> 00:03:00,900
[GIO] I know!

70
00:03:02,367 --> 00:03:04,333
It's the two of you
who aren't thinking.

71
00:03:06,433 --> 00:03:08,533
If he gets the maps,
he's not going to stop

72
00:03:08,533 --> 00:03:11,533
- until he gets the treasure.
- I don't care, Gio!

73
00:03:12,367 --> 00:03:13,400
I don't care!

74
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:16,467
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

75
00:03:16,467 --> 00:03:17,567
Why?

76
00:03:18,867 --> 00:03:21,167
Are you sure he won't kill
your sisters

77
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,533
once he gets the maps?

78
00:03:24,967 --> 00:03:26,733
He's killed a lot of people!

79
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:31,733
As long as we have the maps,
he won't kill Cheska and Trixie.

80
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:34,933
- We have time to look for them!
- Like, hell, there is.

81
00:03:36,433 --> 00:03:39,300
I'll do anything to save
my sister!

82
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:41,267
We have to tell this
to the police.

83
00:03:42,267 --> 00:03:43,900
They know what to do.

84
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:45,767
- Try it.
- I really will.

85
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:47,467
Go and tell it
to the police.

86
00:03:47,467 --> 00:03:53,400
[MUSIC TURNS STIRRING]

87
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,400
[KIKO SIGHS]

88
00:03:56,900 --> 00:03:59,367
[MARTIN BREATHES DEEPLY]

89
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:08,467
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

90
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:02,033
What?!

91
00:05:02,033 --> 00:05:04,300
Martin decided to give
the clues

92
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:06,000
to save Trixie and Cheska.

93
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:09,667
- Did they tell the police?
- This is what I've been saying.

94
00:05:09,667 --> 00:05:11,567
It's 'cause you keep going out!

95
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:17,000
Look at what happened to them.
They can't go home anymore.

96
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,500
Luna, don't say that.

97
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:21,533
Everyone who goes out
don't come home!

98
00:05:21,533 --> 00:05:23,333
No one in this family
is going out!

99
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:24,500
Luna, calm down.

100
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:26,633
No one in this family
is going out!

101
00:05:26,633 --> 00:05:30,433
- Luna!
- Jade, follow your sister. Go.

102
00:05:31,633 --> 00:05:33,867
- Mom, I'll go to the others.
- Wait, Justin!

103
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:40,533
Don't give your sister a reason
to worry.

104
00:05:40,533 --> 00:05:42,633
We'll ask for updates,
but please.

105
00:05:43,467 --> 00:05:44,767
Don't leave.

106
00:05:44,767 --> 00:05:46,000
[FRIDA EXHALES]

107
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:50,767
Luna? Luna?

108
00:05:51,567 --> 00:05:52,700
Lu--

109
00:05:53,433 --> 00:05:56,000
- Luna? Luna, Luna, Luna.
- [CHAIR SCRAPES]

110
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,033
[LUNA] Jade? Jade,
don't go out.

111
00:05:58,967 --> 00:06:01,033
Dad went out,
and didn't come home.

112
00:06:01,033 --> 00:06:04,333
Leon went out,
and didn't come home.

113
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,667
Jade, everyone who goes out
turns dead.

114
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:08,700
Luna, that's not true.

115
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:11,767
It's true. It's true, Jade.
[CRIES]

116
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:12,767
[HUSHED] Luna...

117
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:17,367
We cannot live in fear.

118
00:06:20,367 --> 00:06:21,767
Yes, Dad's gone.

119
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,833
Yes, Leon's gone.

120
00:06:26,433 --> 00:06:27,600
[HUSHED] But Luna...

121
00:06:29,133 --> 00:06:32,000
Our lives won't stop.

122
00:06:32,967 --> 00:06:35,600
- But Jade--
- Luna...

123
00:06:37,533 --> 00:06:38,833
I'm very sure...

124
00:06:39,667 --> 00:06:41,433
Dad and Leon won't like it...

125
00:06:42,133 --> 00:06:45,667
that, yes, we may be alive...

126
00:06:47,100 --> 00:06:50,700
- ...but we live in cages.
- I'm scared to go out, Jade.

127
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,533
- Luna--
- I don't want to go out.

128
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:57,000
Luna, I'm here. No, I'm here.
I'm here for you.

129
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,867
I'm here, Luna.
I'm never going to leave you.

130
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:02,933
[LUNA CRYING]

131
00:07:02,933 --> 00:07:06,833
Justin and I are here.
Mom and I are here for you.

132
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:08,667
And there are a lot
of people outside

133
00:07:08,667 --> 00:07:11,533
waiting for us
to be with them.

134
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:16,400
[LUNA CRYING]

135
00:07:16,433 --> 00:07:17,433
Luna...

136
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:20,067
It's okay to be scared.

137
00:07:21,133 --> 00:07:22,167
[JADE CRIES SOFTLY]

138
00:07:22,167 --> 00:07:23,467
But Luna...

139
00:07:24,467 --> 00:07:27,200
I need you to come back, please.

140
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,800
[LUNA CRYING]

141
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:33,500
I need you, Luna.
Please, for Mom?

142
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:34,933
For this family, Luna.

143
00:07:34,933 --> 00:07:37,500
For me, please.
I need my sister back.

144
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:42,000
I need my sister back, please.
I need-- I need you, Luna.

145
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,700
Come back, please.

146
00:07:44,733 --> 00:07:45,967
Come back.

147
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:50,167
I'm-- I'm here, Jade, I'm sorry.

148
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,700
I'm here now.
Stop crying.

149
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:59,700
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

150
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:02,967
Gio.

151
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,700
[CHAIR CREAKS]

152
00:08:16,767 --> 00:08:17,700
Oh, Gio.

153
00:08:17,933 --> 00:08:19,467
What brings you here?

154
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:20,800
Do you need anything?

155
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:27,700
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

156
00:08:30,033 --> 00:08:31,500
There's a problem, sir.

157
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:34,067
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:08:34,067 --> 00:08:36,000
[LINE RINGING]

159
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:43,733
[PHONE RINGING]

160
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,133
[SOBS]

161
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,200
[PHONE THUDS]

162
00:09:01,233 --> 00:09:03,667
[SOBBING] Martin...

163
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:06,000
<i> Bro, bro, help us.</i>

164
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,267
No, Trixie!

165
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:08,900
Trixie, I'm here.

166
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:10,133
- I'm right here!
<i> - Ma!</i>

167
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:12,100
[GEORGIA]
Cheska, dear, hang in there.

168
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:13,567
Just hang in there.

169
00:09:14,733 --> 00:09:16,133
We'll give you what you want.

170
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,200
What will you do to our sisters?

171
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:23,200
Give me the map
and I'll set them free.

172
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:27,200
Who the hell are you?!

173
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,700
[GEORGIA] Show yourself!

174
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,767
<i>I'll send the pictures
of the map that we found.</i>

175
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,833
<i> We'll do it! We'll do it!</i>

176
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:38,067
<i> Trixie! Trixie, I'm here!</i>

177
00:09:38,067 --> 00:09:40,967
[GEORGIA] Cheska.
Cheska, dear, hang in there.

178
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:42,900
- [PHONE CHIMES]
- [CHESKA] Let us go!

179
00:09:47,033 --> 00:09:48,633
[CHESKA CRYING] Let us go.

180
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,900
Let us go!

181
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:58,100
- Cheska?
- Hello?

182
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,767
Hello?!

183
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,900
[CRYING] Let us go!

184
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,267
Let us go!

185
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:12,167
Kiko, your sister! [CRYING]

186
00:10:17,133 --> 00:10:18,567
Your sister!

187
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:20,900
Your sister, Kiko. [CRYING]

188
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:23,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

189
00:10:25,733 --> 00:10:28,167
Gio, what happened
at Hotel 88?

190
00:10:28,167 --> 00:10:35,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

191
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:37,433
The problem is...

192
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:42,167
we'd like to open
the hotel, sir.

193
00:10:42,167 --> 00:10:43,667
Have you guys found Sandro?

194
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,133
Not yet.

195
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:49,967
But we won't stop
until we find him.

196
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:53,200
- [HENRI] Is that all?
- Yes.

197
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,067
Thank you, sir.

198
00:10:56,067 --> 00:10:59,267
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

199
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:03,633
[PHONE RINGING]

200
00:11:04,533 --> 00:11:06,000
<i> Grandma.</i>

201
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,300
<i> Gio, dear...</i>

202
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:08,633
<i> How are you?</i>

203
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:14,033
I went out, but I'm on my
way back to the hotel.

204
00:11:14,733 --> 00:11:16,733
What about you?
Are you okay?

205
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,667
<i> Yes, I'm okay.</i>

206
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:23,333
<i>But I'm worried
about you.</i>

207
00:11:23,333 --> 00:11:26,067
<i> Just come back home, dear.</i>

208
00:11:26,067 --> 00:11:27,133
Why, Grandma?

209
00:11:27,133 --> 00:11:28,200
Are you sick?

210
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,467
Did something happen?

211
00:11:29,467 --> 00:11:30,700
<i> No.</i>

212
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:33,700
<i> But I'm worried about you
being there.</i>

213
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:37,233
<i>I heard many people have
died there at Hotel 88.</i>

214
00:11:38,267 --> 00:11:39,567
Grandma.

215
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:43,467
<i>Come back home.
What if you end up dead, too?</i>

216
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:45,233
<i> Leave that hotel.</i>

217
00:11:45,233 --> 00:11:47,433
<i> Forget about your inheritance.</i>

218
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:52,067
Grandma, I'm not here
for the money.

219
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,233
I'm here for my brothers.

220
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:56,300
I can't leave them.

221
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:58,300
<i> Then you all leave together.</i>

222
00:11:59,733 --> 00:12:01,400
It's not that easy, Grandma.

223
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,533
But I'll be careful.

224
00:12:06,533 --> 00:12:08,800
I promise I'll come home.

225
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,767
My brothers need me
right now.

226
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,133
I have to be here
for them.

227
00:12:15,433 --> 00:12:17,733
Andy says he has nothing
to do with this.

228
00:12:17,733 --> 00:12:19,800
He said Sandro
is working alone,

229
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:22,300
and he doesn't know
where he's hiding.

230
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:25,600
Son, are you okay?

231
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,767
Kiko.

232
00:12:26,767 --> 00:12:28,667
- [GAGS, COUGHS]
- Kiko! Kiko!

233
00:12:28,667 --> 00:12:31,400
- Kiko!
- What's happening to him?

234
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:34,400
- Son.
- Kiko.

235
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:35,733
Kiko, just relax.

236
00:12:35,733 --> 00:12:38,100
Your body is still weak.

237
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:39,200
Ma...

238
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,333
[SOBBING] Ma, I'm sorry.

239
00:12:44,133 --> 00:12:47,267
I'm sorry that I allowed
Cheska to stay here,

240
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:50,267
but I wasn't able
to protect her.

241
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:53,267
She got into trouble
because of me.

242
00:12:53,267 --> 00:12:54,833
Son...

243
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:57,467
Ma, I'm sorry.
I'm really sorry.

244
00:12:57,467 --> 00:12:59,700
Son, it's not your fault.

245
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:01,533
Don't blame yourself.

246
00:13:01,533 --> 00:13:05,633
It's not your fault.
You didn't want that to happen.

247
00:13:05,633 --> 00:13:12,667
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [SOBBING]

248
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:16,200
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,733
[SOBBING] Ma...

250
00:13:17,733 --> 00:13:19,700
What about you, Martin?

251
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:22,833
When are you going to
tell your parents?

252
00:13:22,867 --> 00:13:25,367
They have the right
to know this.

253
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:29,300
Give them a call.

254
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:31,733
Go ahead. Call them.

255
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:36,400
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

256
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,533
Martin.

257
00:13:39,667 --> 00:13:40,733
I'll fix this.

258
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:44,167
What do you mean?

259
00:13:46,267 --> 00:13:49,800
Martin, what do you mean
by that?

260
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:52,400
I'll call them
once I fix this.

261
00:13:53,567 --> 00:13:56,733
- Martin...
- I can fix this, Auntie.

262
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:03,933
Son...

263
00:14:03,933 --> 00:14:10,867
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

264
00:14:16,733 --> 00:14:23,700
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,533
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

266
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:41,733
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

267
00:14:41,733 --> 00:14:44,900
- [SCREAMING]
- [THUD, OBJECTS CLATTER]

268
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:47,633
The map is still incomplete!

269
00:14:47,633 --> 00:14:49,767
Your brothers are fooling me!

270
00:14:49,767 --> 00:14:52,600
[CRYING] No, they're not.

271
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:56,733
They always keep their word.
They don't lie.

272
00:14:56,733 --> 00:15:01,000
Those are all the clues we have.
We don't know anything else.

273
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,000
That's the only map
we got.

274
00:15:03,033 --> 00:15:04,667
- Liar!
- No!

275
00:15:04,667 --> 00:15:09,400
What did I tell you about
telling lies?!

276
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:13,033
They didn't lie. They sent you
the map they have.

277
00:15:13,033 --> 00:15:18,033
How can I find the treasure
if there's a missing map?!

278
00:15:18,033 --> 00:15:21,967
- Tell me where it is!
- Please stop. Don't hurt us.

279
00:15:22,767 --> 00:15:26,500
Our brothers didn't lie to you.

280
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:30,000
They don't know anything else
aside from that.

281
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:34,467
You should've said goodbye
to your brothers earlier.

282
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:38,333
- [SCREAMING]
- [CRYING]

283
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:42,767
- Please, that's enough.
- Stop this, please!

284
00:15:45,767 --> 00:15:52,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

285
00:15:55,733 --> 00:15:59,167
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

286
00:16:05,733 --> 00:16:07,667
You were gone the entire day.

287
00:16:09,767 --> 00:16:11,533
Did you report to the police?

288
00:16:14,433 --> 00:16:15,500
No.

289
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:19,033
[SCOFFS]

290
00:16:19,533 --> 00:16:20,800
I swear, I didn't.

291
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:27,667
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

292
00:16:29,733 --> 00:16:31,067
Okay.

293
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:34,100
You two are
more important to me.

294
00:16:39,667 --> 00:16:41,700
I wonder what we can do.

295
00:16:42,367 --> 00:16:44,400
Can't we just look for them?

296
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:46,533
If it were that easy, Sari,

297
00:16:46,533 --> 00:16:50,067
Sir Martin would have
found them by now.

298
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:54,400
I just want to help Sir Martin.

299
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,833
Girl, I think you should
just go home.

300
00:16:57,833 --> 00:17:00,533
Huh? Why would I leave you here?

301
00:17:01,133 --> 00:17:03,433
Things are starting to
get dangerous out here, Sari.

302
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:06,267
Raphie! Raphie!

303
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:09,533
You expect me to go home
and just leave you here?

304
00:17:10,867 --> 00:17:13,467
This place is already
my home, remember?

305
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:17,533
Besides, Monette's already gone.

306
00:17:17,567 --> 00:17:19,567
I've got nothing left to lose.

307
00:17:19,767 --> 00:17:22,167
If anything happens to you,

308
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:24,367
who will take care
of your grandpa?

309
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:27,800
- But, Raphie--
- Sari, please listen to me.

310
00:17:28,367 --> 00:17:30,633
This is what
Sir Martin would want.

311
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:33,133
He'd want you home,
safe and sound.

312
00:17:35,233 --> 00:17:37,467
Go on. Please just go home.

313
00:17:38,867 --> 00:17:41,433
I need to take care of something
in Miss Georgia's room.

314
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:54,367
I already sent
the clues earlier.

315
00:17:54,367 --> 00:17:57,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

316
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:59,533
But he hung up on me.

317
00:17:59,533 --> 00:18:00,833
I knew it!

318
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:02,200
I took the risk!

319
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:04,500
You taught us that, remember?

320
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,633
We're talking about
our sisters here, Gio.

321
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:09,433
[CELLPHONE VIBRATING]

322
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:10,567
Look who's calling.

323
00:18:11,433 --> 00:18:12,500
Answer it!

324
00:18:15,467 --> 00:18:16,433
Hello?

325
00:18:16,433 --> 00:18:17,400
Hello.

326
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:18,433
Trixie!

327
00:18:18,433 --> 00:18:19,567
Chesca!

328
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:22,767
Are you trying to fool me?

329
00:18:27,433 --> 00:18:28,767
What are you talking about?!

330
00:18:28,767 --> 00:18:31,467
We did what you asked!
We gave you the map!

331
00:18:31,467 --> 00:18:33,467
Now, let our sisters go!

332
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:37,367
You didn't give me
the complete map.

333
00:18:37,567 --> 00:18:38,600
[MARTIN]
<i> What are you talking about?!</i>

334
00:18:40,767 --> 00:18:42,567
You're hiding something from me.

335
00:18:42,567 --> 00:18:44,167
You didn't give me
the complete map.

336
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:46,500
We gave you everything we had!

337
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:47,767
Three clues!

338
00:18:47,767 --> 00:18:49,733
Those are the only clues
Papa left us!

339
00:18:50,633 --> 00:18:52,700
[SANDRO] Do you
take me for a fool?

340
00:18:53,967 --> 00:18:55,900
If you're telling the truth,

341
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:59,433
you find the treasure
and give it to me!

342
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:02,367
The deal was just the map.

343
00:19:02,967 --> 00:19:04,733
I changed my mind.

344
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:08,700
Two days...

345
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:11,367
<i> You have two days.</i>

346
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:13,367
[MUSIC SWELLS]

347
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:15,467
Two days?

348
00:19:15,667 --> 00:19:17,300
That's not enough time!

349
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:18,900
<i> One day.</i>

350
00:19:18,900 --> 00:19:22,367
<i>Give me the treasure
in one day...</i>

351
00:19:22,367 --> 00:19:24,800
...if you still want to see
these two alive.

352
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,600
[CHESCA] Please help us!

353
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,833
- Aah!
- [TRIXIE] Somebody save us!

354
00:19:28,867 --> 00:19:30,033
Wait!

355
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:31,367
Hold on! Trixie!

356
00:19:31,367 --> 00:19:32,467
Chesca!

357
00:19:32,667 --> 00:19:36,533
- Let us go!
- Please stop this!

358
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:42,233
- We're begging you!
- Let us go!

359
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:48,667
Aah!

360
00:19:48,667 --> 00:19:51,333
- [THUDS]
- Martin!

361
00:19:51,333 --> 00:19:53,267
Losing your cool won't help us!

362
00:19:53,267 --> 00:19:54,667
Those are our sisters!

363
00:19:54,667 --> 00:19:57,233
Gio, it's our sisters
we're talking about here!

364
00:20:02,467 --> 00:20:04,267
We'll give him the treasure.

365
00:20:06,967 --> 00:20:09,000
That's the only way
to get them back.

366
00:20:10,967 --> 00:20:17,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:20:25,733 --> 00:20:30,067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

368
00:20:30,067 --> 00:20:32,067
[MARTIN BREATHING SHARPLY]

369
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:33,633
This doesn't make sense.

370
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,400
Calm down so you can
think clearly.

371
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:39,100
I am calm, okay?

372
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:42,067
Wait. Cheska already
did this before.

373
00:20:42,067 --> 00:20:43,567
We'll just continue it.

374
00:20:45,633 --> 00:20:48,533
What if Sandro's right?
What if there's a missing map?

375
00:20:48,533 --> 00:20:50,100
How can that be?

376
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,533
Papa left three clues.

377
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:53,700
We got three maps.
They're all complete.

378
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:55,167
What if there was
a fourth map?

379
00:20:55,167 --> 00:20:57,067
Then where and how can
we get it?

380
00:20:57,067 --> 00:20:59,433
Papa only left three clues.

381
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:03,433
If both Papa and Uncle Fred
knew where to find the treasure,

382
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:06,667
how come it was only Papa
who kept the clues?

383
00:21:06,667 --> 00:21:08,033
And your point is?

384
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:10,467
If Papa kept some clues,

385
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:13,100
then Uncle Fred might have
done the same.

386
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:15,433
It might lead us
to the fourth map.

387
00:21:15,433 --> 00:21:17,733
Luna never mentioned
anything about it.

388
00:21:18,667 --> 00:21:21,200
We didn't know about these
clues either.

389
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,067
But we still managed
to find them, right?

390
00:21:23,067 --> 00:21:24,767
It's probably in their house.

391
00:21:24,767 --> 00:21:27,367
Okay, I'll call Luna.

392
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:32,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

393
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:35,133
Kiko, I know it's hard but you
have to stay strong.

394
00:21:35,133 --> 00:21:37,500
- I'm trying.
- Try harder.

395
00:21:40,567 --> 00:21:42,100
Remember what Papa said?

396
00:21:43,367 --> 00:21:45,567
Only the brave can find
the Easter egg.

397
00:21:50,133 --> 00:21:52,400
Finding it requires bravery
and determination.

398
00:21:57,433 --> 00:21:58,767
Kiko, you're brave.

399
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:02,233
I know we'll find Cheska.

400
00:22:05,867 --> 00:22:07,400
We'll save her and Trixie.

401
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:13,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

402
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:21,833
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

403
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:27,633
[TRIXIE] No.

404
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:29,733
Don't leave that here
with us.

405
00:22:29,733 --> 00:22:31,267
Please, don't.

406
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,800
They will give you
the treasure.

407
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:36,767
Please let us go.

408
00:22:36,767 --> 00:22:40,300
- Trust me.
- Please, we're begging you.

409
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:43,600
You'll get the treasure.
Please let us go.

410
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,767
[TRIXIE]
Please, we're begging you.

411
00:22:45,767 --> 00:22:47,267
I'll give you one day.

412
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,833
[CHESKA] Please.

413
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:53,767
- No, please.
- Help!

414
00:22:53,767 --> 00:22:57,667
- Please let us go.
- Someone help us!

415
00:22:57,667 --> 00:22:59,300
Please, we're begging you.

416
00:23:02,233 --> 00:23:03,633
<i> If Papa kept some clues,</i>

417
00:23:03,633 --> 00:23:05,300
<i>then Uncle Fred might
have done the same.</i>

418
00:23:05,300 --> 00:23:07,200
<i>It might lead us to
the fourth map.</i>

419
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:09,700
<i>I searched the cabinets,
the rooms, and Dad's office,</i>

420
00:23:09,700 --> 00:23:11,233
<i> but still nothing.</i>

421
00:23:11,233 --> 00:23:13,333
<i> They're just here, dear.</i>

422
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:14,900
<i> They're not far away.</i>

423
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:19,800
<i>If your families won't give me
what I need,</i>

424
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:22,367
<i> I'll go to another family.</i>

425
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,500
<i>- No!
- No!</i>

426
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:25,933
<i> - No!
- No, Uncle Andy!</i>

427
00:23:25,933 --> 00:23:29,267
<i>Please, just give it to me.
I need the map.</i>

428
00:23:29,267 --> 00:23:30,833
<i>Just give it to me.
Give it to me.</i>
